William L. BENSON and William H. Hutcheson, Appellants, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 11363. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 25, 1946. Fred McDonald, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellants. Frank J. Henn'essy, U. S. Atty., and Reynold H. Colvin, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, BONE, and ORR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeals in this cause be and hereby are dismissed, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
